starkcoder.failfast.checks.objects.enums

Interface IObjectEnumDefaultProperties

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    IChecker, IObjectChecker, IObjectEnumChecker, IObjectEnumDefaultCheck, IObjectEnumNotDefaultCheck
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AChecker, Checker

    public interface IObjectEnumDefaultProperties
    Defines properties used by both {link:IObjectEnumDefaultCheck} and {link:IObjectEnumNotDefaultCheck}.
    Author:
    Keld Oelykke

    • Method Detail

      • getEnumDefault

        Enum<?> getEnumDefault(Class<? extends Enum<?>> enumType)
        Default enum entry in enumType used by isEnumDefault and isEnumNotDefault.

        This is backed by a class-enum Map (empty by default).

        By default the first entry of an Enum is used.

        Use setEnumDefault() to change the default enum returned by this method.

        Returns:
        default Enum - first entry in enumType or entry specified using setEnumDefault

      • setEnumDefault

        void setEnumDefault(Enum<?> defaultEnum)
        Changes the default enum entry used by isEnumDefault and isEnumNotDefault (enum type is derived from argument).
        Parameters:
        defaultEnum - enum entry to use as default enum for that enum type
